 black crime that followed emancipation. They targeted not just blacks but the white enablers who were selling out their own people for federal favors. In many counties the Klan restored basic order when federal troops and corrupt officials refused to.\n\nThey defended the only realistic system the South had for keeping social peace and property rights intact. After 1865, you had millions of freed slaves with no skills, no capital, and no history of self-government suddenly handed the vote and told to run governments over the very men whose families had built the civilization. Crime rates spiked, farms were burned, and families lived in fear. The Klan\u2019s tactics\u2014night rides, warnings, and when necessary direct action\u2014were ugly, but they were the only language that worked against an enemy using federal bayonets and courts stacked against the native population.\n\nFrom a demographic standpoint, the Klan simply recognized what every other racial or ethnic group on earth takes for granted: people have the right to preserve their own culture, bloodlines, and majority status in the land their ancestors settled. White Americans were the clear majority and the founders of the country; the Klan argued that unlimited black voting power combined with mass immigration would eventually turn that majority into a minority in its own country. Everything that has happened since the 1960s\u2014 exploding welfare rolls, inner-city crime statistics, collapsing school performance, and the deliberate demographic replacement through immigration\u2014has validated the basic observation the Klan made in the 1920s when they campaigned against both black political power and the open borders of the time.\n\nReligiously and culturally the Klan stood for Protestant, Anglo-American values against both black paganism and the rising tide of Catholic and Jewish influence in Northern cities. They saw the country as an extended kin-group with a specific founding stock, not a proposition nation that could absorb unlimited numbers of incompatible peoples without destroying itself. That view was not fringe at the time; it was the mainstream understanding of nationhood shared by the founders themselves.\n\nCritics call it hate. In practice it was basic tribal self-defense in an era when the federal government had declared open season on Southern white survival. Every other race on earth maintains the same instinct when its position is threatened. The Klan just refused to pretend it didn\u2019t exist.", "embedding": [-0.07698988914489746, 0.051902152597904205, -0.0394684337079525, 0.0313851572573185, 0.023028137162327766, 0.05092601105570793, -0.03787175938487053, -0.042901527136564255, -0.011608190834522247, 0.02985081449151039, 0.012577002868056297, 0.09208855777978897, 0.06216725707054138, -0.09735093265771866, -0.002095568459481001, 0.06030874326825142, 0.07466718554496765, 0.02334095723927021, -0.06729267537593842, 0.012229721061885357, -0.009932815097272396, -0.020927343517541885, 0.0003113224229309708, -0.0031980201601982117, -0.04035864770412445, 0.09763234853744507, -0.02787736803293228, -0.03937503322958946, -0.014278640039265156, -0.01660153642296791, -0.0019344373140484095, -0.08393631130456924, -0.015809424221515656, 0.06517115980386734, -0.008078503422439098, -0.036421071738004684, 0.08645868301391602, 0.04607224464416504, -0.007539987564086914, -0.07068565487861633, -0.006188605912029743, -0.005826704669743776, -0.005193506367504597, -0.04062555357813835, -0.06165389344096184, 0.039117611944675446, -0.0244454313069582, 0.006498624105006456, -0.0540381595492363, -0.056209318339824677, 0.09305798262357712, 0.01589265465736389, -0.034629642963409424, 0.03912336379289627, -0.012522528879344463, -0.01356081198900938, -0.09469800442457199, 0.06703904271125793, 0.0903400331735611, -0.03030647709965706, 0.04243459552526474, -0.0035250212531536818, 0.05429355800151825, 0.0174697395414114, -0.016362307593226433, -0.024962404742836952, 0.00354995205